HEADWORD: Gemmy
<hw>Gem"my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Gem</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of gems; bright; glittering like a
gem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>gemmy</qex> bridle glittered free.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Spruce; smart.</def> <mark>[Colloq. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gemote</ent>⟦br⟧
